1
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,240
One, two, three, four, five.

2
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,800
Have pork prices gone up or something?

3
00:00:43,000 --> 00:00:45,560
Type! Tharn! Over here! Come here!

4
00:00:45,920 --> 00:00:48,720
I got us a table. Come sit here.

5
00:00:58,040 --> 00:01:01,280
Lately, the two of you've been
pretty cozy.

6
00:01:03,640 --> 00:01:04,920
Isn't that good?

7
00:01:05,240 --> 00:01:07,840
You can finally stop complaining about us.

8
00:01:10,000 --> 00:01:11,600
It's good.

9
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:15,440
But you guys seem very, very close.

10
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,240
Type!

11
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:21,080
You already have a girlfriend?

12
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:22,400
You have a girlfriend?

13
00:01:24,760 --> 00:01:25,760
Yeah.

14
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:30,080
Fai said Type gave her false hope.

15
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:36,080
It's true. I'm sorry.

16
00:01:37,400 --> 00:01:39,120
Why didn't you tell her before?

17
00:01:39,520 --> 00:01:41,200
She's really hurt, you know?

18
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:44,200
Anyway…

19
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:47,320
It's my fault for introducing them
to each other.

20
00:01:48,920 --> 00:01:51,760
And don't call her to apologize again.

21
00:01:53,040 --> 00:01:54,760
Or else she'll give you an earful.

22
00:01:55,920 --> 00:01:56,960
Okay.

23
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:00,400
By the way, who's your girlfriend?

24
00:02:00,600 --> 00:02:02,320
Yeah, who is it?

25
00:02:10,640 --> 00:02:12,200
Why do I have to tell you?

26
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:15,080
Aren't we friends? Do I know her?

27
00:02:15,480 --> 00:02:17,760
If you don't stop questioning me,

28
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:20,400
you won't finish breakfast
in time for class.

29
00:02:21,080 --> 00:02:21,920
Stingy.

30
00:02:22,520 --> 00:02:24,840
I'm gonna buy breakfast. Be right back.

31
00:02:36,200 --> 00:02:38,520
Let's talk about your "girlfriend," Type.

32
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,640
If my hunch is correct…

33
00:02:42,640 --> 00:02:44,360
that person is…

34
00:02:45,440 --> 00:02:46,680
Have some water, Techno.

35
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,400
You look thirsty.

36
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,440
I'm not thirsty!

37
00:02:53,160 --> 00:02:55,080
The person you're dating, Type…

38
00:02:56,680 --> 00:02:57,560
Is it--

39
00:02:57,720 --> 00:02:59,640
I think you should drink some more.

40
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,640
You look really parched.

41
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:04,520
Hold on! Don't change the subject.

42
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:06,840
Don't you dare keep secrets from me.

43
00:03:07,440 --> 00:03:08,480
What secrets?

44
00:03:08,880 --> 00:03:11,040
Yeah, what secrets?

45
00:03:13,040 --> 00:03:15,080
Don't team up against me!

46
00:03:16,920 --> 00:03:19,000
The one you're dating, Type,

47
00:03:19,240 --> 00:03:20,600
that person is--

48
00:03:22,760 --> 00:03:24,320
The line was frickin' long.

49
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:26,080
Why are there so many people?

50
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,760
Then…

51
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,760
You guys can keep talking.

52
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:31,240
I have to go to class.

53
00:03:31,520 --> 00:03:35,680
Remember, we have to sign
the contract for the dorm this evening.

54
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,960
Then, I'll call you after class.

55
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,200
See you.

56
00:03:42,520 --> 00:03:43,400
Wait a minute.

57
00:03:43,560 --> 00:03:45,160
Dorm? What dorm?

58
00:03:45,560 --> 00:03:47,240
I'm moving off campus with Tharn.

59
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,040
You're moving off campus with Tharn?

60
00:03:52,120 --> 00:03:53,280
By the way, Techno,

61
00:03:54,160 --> 00:03:55,320
your hunch…

62
00:03:57,240 --> 00:03:58,360
is correct.

63
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:35,840
Type, what do you want?

64
00:05:36,520 --> 00:05:37,920
Nothing much.

65
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:39,000
Is Seo here?

66
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:40,480
Yes.

67
00:05:41,400 --> 00:05:43,480
Seo Duang, Type's here to see you.

68
00:05:49,720 --> 00:05:51,200
What's the matter?

69
00:05:52,040 --> 00:05:54,200
It's semester break.
Why don't you go home?

70
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,320
That's the reason we're here.

71
00:05:56,760 --> 00:05:57,680
The thing is,

72
00:05:57,960 --> 00:05:59,880
we came here to say goodbye.

73
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:01,000
You're dropping out?

74
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,680
Do you really have to drop out?

75
00:06:04,240 --> 00:06:05,600
Please, think this through.

76
00:06:06,080 --> 00:06:07,040
Khlui!

77
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,280
-Khlui.
-Yeah.

78
00:06:09,440 --> 00:06:10,880
They haven't finished yet.

79
00:06:11,640 --> 00:06:13,800
Where are you going? Finish your sentence.

80
00:06:14,240 --> 00:06:15,800
We're gonna move off campus.

81
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:19,960
And you're moving in together?

82
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:21,440
That's right.

83
00:06:21,680 --> 00:06:24,520
We're moving in together.

84
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:29,800
It's because you guys said
the wall's thin.

85
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:32,520
We fight a lot,
so we don't want to bother you.

86
00:06:34,960 --> 00:06:40,040
So you're going to move in
to a room with thick…

87
00:06:40,720 --> 00:06:42,440
and soundproof walls, aren't you?

88
00:06:42,520 --> 00:06:43,960
You got it wrong!

89
00:06:47,840 --> 00:06:50,160
Good for you. Good.

90
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,600
Come here.

91
00:06:55,080 --> 00:06:56,800
When you live together,

92
00:06:57,240 --> 00:07:01,320
no matter how much you argue,
always forgive each other.

93
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:06,120
Fighting is part of a couple's life.

94
00:07:06,760 --> 00:07:07,960
It's a fact.

95
00:07:09,240 --> 00:07:11,480
What are you saying?

96
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:18,560
As the person who's been watching you
from the beginning,

97
00:07:19,800 --> 00:07:21,720
I'm so happy for you.

98
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,840
That's enough.

99
00:07:31,520 --> 00:07:33,240
They're not getting married.

100
00:07:34,440 --> 00:07:35,280
You bastard.

101
00:07:37,240 --> 00:07:38,560
Anyway, I'm happy for you.

102
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,520
Thank you so much.

103
00:07:41,160 --> 00:07:42,320
We have to go.

104
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,000
Goodbye.

105
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:44,920
Goodbye.

106
00:07:46,760 --> 00:07:48,200
Good luck.

107
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,400
It hurts.

108
00:08:03,560 --> 00:08:04,560
Khlui!

109
00:08:05,360 --> 00:08:07,320
Stop crying and start packing.

110
00:08:08,640 --> 00:08:10,880
Didn't you say you're going home tomorrow?

111
00:08:11,800 --> 00:08:13,320
I'm happy.

112
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:15,040
Seo.

113
00:08:15,560 --> 00:08:17,200
You wouldn't understand.

114
00:08:18,560 --> 00:08:20,480
I feel like a father…

115
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,960
who's just walked his two sons…

116
00:08:23,760 --> 00:08:25,520
down the aisle.

117
00:08:39,520 --> 00:08:41,280
They got their happy ending.

118
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:43,920
So…

119
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:46,680
when will you stop paying attention
to other people…

120
00:08:47,160 --> 00:08:49,680
and start paying attention
to someone close to you?

121
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,440
Who is it?

122
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:03,720
I…

123
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:06,440
like you.

124
00:09:14,960 --> 00:09:17,440
<i>Zoo-wah-hey?</i>

125
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:19,960
What does that mean?

126
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:23,960
What's so funny?

127
00:09:26,000 --> 00:09:27,160
Nothing.

128
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:30,880
I'm glad you let me tell Techno about us.

129
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:35,000
He's gonna find out anyway.

130
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:38,120
You don't have to feel
extremely grateful to me.

131
00:09:39,760 --> 00:09:43,120
And other than him, I don't want
anybody else to know just yet.

132
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:48,640
After we're done moving…

133
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:50,720
I'm going back to Pha-ngan.

134
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,280
I made a promise to my dad.

135
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:57,800
Li'l Type is going home to see his daddy?

136
00:10:01,320 --> 00:10:03,200
-Asshole.
-You're asking for it.

137
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:06,760
Keep packing.

138
00:10:20,240 --> 00:10:22,080
I'm home!

139
00:10:24,120 --> 00:10:27,280
Four months with Tharn
really bored me to death.

140
00:10:27,520 --> 00:10:29,320
A month away from him is all I need.

141
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:31,200
Pup!

142
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,560
You went nuts from studying too hard?

143
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,320
Is that why you're yelling here?

144
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:41,440
I just needed to vent my frustration.

145
00:10:45,920 --> 00:10:47,600
Frustrated with your love life?

146
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:50,360
Right, you got dumped by a girl.

147
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:53,760
Come on, Dad, that's in the past.
Just forget about it.

148
00:10:53,840 --> 00:10:55,520
How can I forget?

149
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:58,160
I transferred 2,000 baht to you,

150
00:10:58,440 --> 00:11:01,040
but you came back empty-handed. Useless.

151
00:11:01,480 --> 00:11:06,200
When I was your age, I didn't need money
to make women chase after me.

152
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,080
Women or dogs?

153
00:11:08,240 --> 00:11:11,000
Brat! How could you say that
to your father?

154
00:11:11,240 --> 00:11:13,120
Just shut your mouth.

155
00:11:13,680 --> 00:11:15,640
So when will you return to Bangkok?

156
00:11:16,280 --> 00:11:20,080
Dad, I've just arrived
and you want me gone already?

157
00:11:20,440 --> 00:11:22,680
No, I'm just asking.

158
00:11:23,080 --> 00:11:24,720
Because I'll give you a ride.

159
00:11:24,960 --> 00:11:28,280
By the way, you finally moved
off campus, huh?

160
00:11:28,520 --> 00:11:29,960
Stubborn pup.

161
00:11:31,160 --> 00:11:33,040
The friend you've moved in with…

162
00:11:33,360 --> 00:11:34,680
What's he like?

163
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:40,320
He has nothing but good looks.

164
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,280
He's annoyingly attentive.

165
00:11:44,240 --> 00:11:48,440
Normally, he's cool and calm like ice.

166
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,720
But when he gets angry,
all hell breaks loose.

167
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:54,840
And he's stubborn.

168
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:57,680
He does everything for me
when I tell him not to.

169
00:11:57,760 --> 00:12:00,640
He buys me food when I tell him not to.

170
00:12:00,800 --> 00:12:03,920
He hangs up my laundry
when I tell him not to.

171
00:12:04,160 --> 00:12:06,440
He even changes my bed sheets.

172
00:12:08,080 --> 00:12:08,920
And…

173
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:10,960
he has nothing but good looks.

174
00:12:11,160 --> 00:12:14,040
He's a quarter American.
His dad is half American.

175
00:12:14,480 --> 00:12:16,880
His large nose almost pokes my face.

176
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:22,560
And he's especially popular with women
when he plays in his band.

177
00:12:24,280 --> 00:12:28,160
From what you've told me,
it sounds like you two are really close.

178
00:12:28,880 --> 00:12:30,280
Who says we're close?

179
00:12:30,640 --> 00:12:34,600
If you're not close,
then why would he do everything for you?

180
00:12:35,400 --> 00:12:39,160
Besides, you even know about his family.

181
00:12:39,760 --> 00:12:43,560
You never gave this many details
about your other friends before.

182
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:49,000
I still don't know
what Team and Oam look like.

183
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,640
Never mind.

184
00:12:51,000 --> 00:12:54,280
But it looks like you really admire
this friend of yours.

185
00:12:55,280 --> 00:12:56,840
Who says I admire him?

186
00:12:58,680 --> 00:13:01,560
You just complimented him non-stop.

187
00:13:05,280 --> 00:13:06,200
Dad,

188
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,400
a guest wants to talk to you.

189
00:13:08,760 --> 00:13:10,440
He's white, not Middle Eastern.

190
00:13:10,560 --> 00:13:11,680
You know what I meant.

191
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,240
Okay, I'll go take care of the guest.

192
00:13:14,320 --> 00:13:16,640
And don't just lay around.

193
00:13:16,760 --> 00:13:19,840
Because we're very busy
with all the Westerners coming.

194
00:13:20,000 --> 00:13:21,080
Okay.

195
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:50,760
<i>Hello?</i>

196
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:51,840
Hello.

197
00:13:52,120 --> 00:13:53,320
<i>Miss me?</i>

198
00:13:53,640 --> 00:13:56,040
Jerk, don't get on my nerves.

199
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,560
<i>When did I do that?</i>

200
00:13:57,680 --> 00:13:58,680
<i>I was just asking.</i>

201
00:13:59,760 --> 00:14:01,360
Then, my answer is no.

202
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:04,520
We just saw each other yesterday.
How can I miss you?

203
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,840
<i>Exactly.</i>

204
00:14:06,160 --> 00:14:09,880
<i>We just saw each other,</i>
<i>but you're calling me already.</i>

205
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:12,040
Jerk.

206
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:15,920
<i>Are you home yet? How was your trip?</i>

207
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,120
Worried about me?

208
00:14:20,000 --> 00:14:22,160
<i>I'm both worried and possessive about you.</i>

209
00:14:23,320 --> 00:14:27,000
No matter how much you sweet-talk me,
I'll never fall for it.

210
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,960
<i>But you've fallen for my mouth.</i>

211
00:14:30,920 --> 00:14:32,080
I told you.

212
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:35,640
I won't fall for your sweet-talk,
no matter how much you do it.

213
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,440
<i>I'm not talking about sweet-talk.</i>

214
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:39,560
<i>I'm talking about my mouth…</i>

215
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:41,680
<i>when I kiss you.</i>

216
00:14:42,160 --> 00:14:43,480
Go to hell, asshole!

217
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:48,080
What total bullshit!

218
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,640
I really hate you with all my guts.

219
00:15:14,360 --> 00:15:16,840
Did you finish talking
with your friend, Tharn?

220
00:15:17,120 --> 00:15:18,080
Yes, I did.

221
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:19,680
Let me see.

222
00:15:19,760 --> 00:15:21,960
Which part of the song are you practicing?

223
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:24,040
I can already play the whole song.

224
00:15:24,200 --> 00:15:26,840
Next week, the teacher
will teach me a new song.

225
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:30,280
Don't return to your dorm just yet.

226
00:15:30,520 --> 00:15:32,840
Stay and watch me
practice the new song first.

227
00:15:35,840 --> 00:15:37,080
Actually…

228
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:39,480
I have band practice next week.

229
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:43,960
I'm not sure if I can watch you practice.

230
00:15:44,720 --> 00:15:46,400
You have to leave again?

231
00:15:47,040 --> 00:15:50,840
I miss you so much when you're not around.

232
00:15:53,360 --> 00:15:54,920
I missed you too, Thanya.

233
00:15:55,800 --> 00:15:57,280
I don't believe you.

234
00:15:57,520 --> 00:16:00,280
If you miss me,
why don't you come home more often?

235
00:16:02,840 --> 00:16:06,280
He may miss you,
but he misses something else more.

236
00:16:07,680 --> 00:16:10,360
Hi, Thorn. When did you get back?

237
00:16:11,160 --> 00:16:14,440
When you acted like
you were going to bail on Thanya.

238
00:16:15,720 --> 00:16:19,000
Honestly, you're scolding me…

239
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,520
because you're hurt
Thanya is more attached to me, right?

240
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:30,560
I'm deeply hurt.

241
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:35,800
Whenever Tharn comes back,
you always ignore me.

242
00:16:36,440 --> 00:16:39,000
I already see you every day.

243
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:48,160
Are you really busy
with band practice next week?

244
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:51,840
Partly.

245
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,640
What are you actually busy with?

246
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:57,760
Is it about last month's incident
when you looked gloomy,

247
00:16:57,960 --> 00:17:00,040
as if someone had broken your drum set?

248
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:04,280
So, what happened?

249
00:17:05,400 --> 00:17:07,360
Right now…

250
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:11,760
we're dating.

251
00:17:11,960 --> 00:17:14,280
That's good news.

252
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,000
Of course, it is.

253
00:17:16,480 --> 00:17:18,320
But I was totally exhausted.

254
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:22,520
Come to think of it,
you haven't dated for almost six months.

255
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:25,080
Enough about me.

256
00:17:25,160 --> 00:17:26,560
What about you?

257
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:29,000
There's nothing to talk about.

258
00:17:29,240 --> 00:17:32,440
I don't have time
for anyone else but Thanya.

259
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:35,920
You should find a girlfriend, Thorn.

260
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:37,880
You're already 21.

261
00:17:38,160 --> 00:17:41,240
It's not good for you
to get too attached to me.

262
00:17:41,840 --> 00:17:44,040
What a mean girl.

263
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,320
By the way,
I'm meeting with San this week.

264
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,640
Wanna come with me?

265
00:17:54,360 --> 00:17:56,040
San's back?

266
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,560
He's been back for nearly a month now.

267
00:18:00,520 --> 00:18:02,280
We're meeting up for lunch.

268
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:04,360
He's bringing us souvenirs too.

269
00:18:04,560 --> 00:18:08,280
He said he'd love to see you
if you had the time.

270
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:09,960
He misses you.

271
