Okay.

548
00:41:26,120 --> 00:41:28,840
How can you believe him so easily, Thanya?

549
00:41:29,320 --> 00:41:31,960
I think you played really well.

550
00:41:32,480 --> 00:41:34,920
You're the one I shouldn't believe.

551
00:41:37,120 --> 00:41:38,640
She's right.

552
00:41:39,360 --> 00:41:41,760
You spoil her too much.
Even she can see that.

553
00:41:42,120 --> 00:41:44,760
Come on, Dad. When did I ever spoil her?

554
00:41:45,160 --> 00:41:46,560
I'm just telling the truth.

555
00:41:46,920 --> 00:41:49,320
Sure, the truth.

556
00:41:49,520 --> 00:41:52,160
The truth is you're
an overly attached brother.

557
00:41:53,400 --> 00:41:54,960
Don't you see how cute she is?

558
00:41:55,160 --> 00:41:56,960
Thanks to your skills,

559
00:41:57,200 --> 00:41:59,400
Thanya looks like a living doll.

560
00:42:00,440 --> 00:42:02,680
Don't you know who I am?

561
00:42:04,360 --> 00:42:06,640
What are you two talking about?

562
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,240
I'm going to prepare dinner.

563
00:42:09,440 --> 00:42:12,960
Today, we have a guest coming.
Anybody want anything special?

564
00:42:13,120 --> 00:42:15,760
I can eat whatever you cook.

565
00:42:15,920 --> 00:42:19,560
But can I have Thai food?
I'm getting tired of cheese.

566
00:42:19,720 --> 00:42:23,560
Come on, honey, it's Tharn's favorite.

567
00:42:23,640 --> 00:42:27,440
He comes home so rarely
that I have to treat him especially well.

568
00:42:34,440 --> 00:42:40,280
I'M BACK IN BANGKOK.

569
00:42:40,360 --> 00:42:41,600
Dad, Mom,

570
00:42:42,040 --> 00:42:44,880
I won't stay for dinner today.
I'm going back to my dorm.

571
00:42:47,720 --> 00:42:48,840
I'm heading out.

572
00:42:51,120 --> 00:42:54,480
Tharn, San's coming today.

573
00:42:54,680 --> 00:42:56,280
I thought you'd stay to see him.

574
00:42:56,560 --> 00:42:57,880
Then…

575
00:42:58,120 --> 00:42:59,840
tell him I'm sorry.

576
00:43:00,320 --> 00:43:01,400
I have to go.

577
00:43:01,800 --> 00:43:04,000
Don't know when I'll be back. Bye.

578
00:43:08,920 --> 00:43:11,240
Why is Tharn in such a hurry, Thorn?

579
00:43:13,840 --> 00:43:15,640
Judging from his excitement…

580
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:18,520
it's easy to guess who he's going to see.

581
00:43:19,040 --> 00:43:21,440
Come on, let him be happy.

582
00:43:21,560 --> 00:43:23,120
What else can we do?

583
00:43:25,960 --> 00:43:28,440
Okay, I'm going to prepare dinner.

584
00:44:02,760 --> 00:44:04,080
You're late.

585
00:44:05,720 --> 00:44:07,960
Am I really late?

586
00:44:10,560 --> 00:44:12,520
I thought you'd come here…

587
00:44:13,400 --> 00:44:14,960
as soon as I texted you.

588
00:44:16,560 --> 00:44:18,440
I tried to call you many times,

589
00:44:19,000 --> 00:44:20,320
but you didn't pick up.

590
00:44:21,720 --> 00:44:22,920
And I'm not a dog…

591
00:44:23,760 --> 00:44:27,200
who runs to his owner
as soon as he gets home.

592
00:44:28,360 --> 00:44:29,360
You're not?

593
00:44:30,760 --> 00:44:31,720
Not a dog.

594
00:44:33,680 --> 00:44:35,120
But your boyfriend.

595
00:44:41,280 --> 00:44:42,360
What are you wearing?

596
00:44:46,480 --> 00:44:47,960
Your welcome home gift.

597
00:44:51,960 --> 00:44:53,080
Did you…

598
00:44:55,280 --> 00:44:56,320
forget something?

599
00:44:57,640 --> 00:44:58,800
What?

600
00:45:02,360 --> 00:45:03,480
This.

601
00:45:18,000 --> 00:45:19,360
I didn't forget.

602
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:22,880
It's because you were super late.

603
00:45:26,160 --> 00:45:27,320
I'm sorry…

604
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:29,840
for being late.

605
00:46:13,360 --> 00:46:16,280
Dad, why didn't you tell me
you were coming to Bangkok?

606
00:46:16,360 --> 00:46:20,720
And now you want to see me
just before you leave?

607
00:46:21,440 --> 00:46:23,720
I'm outside right now.

608
00:46:24,120 --> 00:46:27,240
<i>What? I told you I was coming to see you.</i>

609
00:46:27,960 --> 00:46:30,320
<i>Besides, I want to meet your friend.</i>

610
00:46:30,960 --> 00:46:34,440
You said you were going back to Pa-ngan,
not stopping by here.

611
00:46:34,640 --> 00:46:36,120
<i>It's the same thing.</i>

612
00:46:36,480 --> 00:46:38,560
<i>We won't see each other for four months.</i>

613
00:46:38,720 --> 00:46:40,360
<i>At least, let me say goodbye.</i>

614
00:46:40,560 --> 00:46:42,280
You can always skip work.

615
00:46:42,560 --> 00:46:46,880
<i>Your mom will chop my head off</i>
<i>if I do that.</i>

616
00:46:48,400 --> 00:46:50,000
Go talk to Mom about it.

617
00:46:50,240 --> 00:46:52,000
Tell her to drive safely.

618
00:46:52,400 --> 00:46:53,240
Bye.

619
00:46:55,520 --> 00:46:58,600
No "li'l Type" this time?

620
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:00,360
Bastard.

621
00:47:00,960 --> 00:47:02,480
Is your dad…

622
00:47:03,480 --> 00:47:04,720
coming to see you?

623
00:47:06,840 --> 00:47:08,520
My aunt's in the hospital.

624
00:47:10,120 --> 00:47:14,480
But she's gotten better,
so my parents will leave Bangkok today.

625
00:47:15,600 --> 00:47:18,320
Actually, he wanted to meet you.

626
00:47:20,120 --> 00:47:21,680
Don't make that face.

627
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:24,680
He just wants to meet my roommate.

628
00:47:27,320 --> 00:47:30,160
Do you seriously think
I'd tell him we're together?

629
00:47:38,520 --> 00:47:39,640
I was hoping…

630
00:47:41,840 --> 00:47:43,360
for the impossible.

631
00:47:48,760 --> 00:47:49,880
I'm sorry.

632
00:47:51,360 --> 00:47:52,480
About what?

633
00:47:55,840 --> 00:47:59,600
About something that needs
to be kept secret forever.

634
00:48:01,240 --> 00:48:02,240
I already knew that.

635
00:48:03,840 --> 00:48:07,080
You'll never tell anyone.

636
00:48:09,760 --> 00:48:11,360
Why are you mad at me?

637
00:48:12,760 --> 00:48:19,120
Does it matter if we tell other people
about our relationship or not?

638
00:48:20,960 --> 00:48:22,680
It may not matter to you…

639
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:25,240
but to me…

640
00:48:26,640 --> 00:48:27,760
it does.

641
00:48:30,880 --> 00:48:34,200
I just want to let people know
you're mine.

642
00:48:35,600 --> 00:48:36,680
That's all.

643
00:48:53,440 --> 00:48:54,280
Here.

644
00:48:55,440 --> 00:48:56,400
I'll let you order.

645
00:48:56,560 --> 00:48:58,200
You want to eat here, don't you?

646
00:49:02,240 --> 00:49:06,920
I'll have the sashimi set,
spicy salmon salad, and…

647
00:49:07,360 --> 00:49:09,480
tuna sushi and rolls, two each.

648
00:49:09,640 --> 00:49:10,520
You want rice?

649
00:49:10,880 --> 00:49:13,240
On second thought,
rice makes you full faster.

650
00:49:13,640 --> 00:49:15,520
I'll just have two miso soups.

651
00:49:16,080 --> 00:49:17,320
What about you?

652
00:49:17,920 --> 00:49:20,200
You only ordered raw dishes.

653
00:49:21,360 --> 00:49:24,280
I'll have grilled mackerel.

654
00:49:24,520 --> 00:49:26,640
-One grilled mackerel.
-That's it.

655
00:49:27,120 --> 00:49:28,840
I'm not finished yet.

656
00:49:29,120 --> 00:49:30,960
You won't be able to eat all of it.

657
00:49:31,840 --> 00:49:33,760
You eat too little.

658
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:37,040
Let's compete to see who can eat more.

659
00:49:38,280 --> 00:49:39,840
Don't be ridiculous, Type.

660
00:49:41,560 --> 00:49:42,680
Anyway…

661
00:49:44,040 --> 00:49:46,200
your hair is longer.

662
00:49:47,480 --> 00:49:49,200
My skin's tanner too.

663
00:49:50,160 --> 00:49:51,040
I know.

664
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:54,360
I can see the Speedo tan line.

665
00:49:54,920 --> 00:49:56,800
What the hell are you thinking about?

666
00:49:57,560 --> 00:49:58,640
No.

667
00:49:59,240 --> 00:50:00,080
Nothing.

668
00:50:02,720 --> 00:50:05,320
Can you really eat everything you ordered?

669
00:50:05,840 --> 00:50:07,880
Of course, they're all my favorites.

670
00:50:08,160 --> 00:50:09,280
I have my doubts.

671
00:50:15,760 --> 00:50:17,920
Here you go.
This is what you wanted, right?

672
00:50:18,800 --> 00:50:21,000
Don't use a girly trick
to make it up to me.

673
00:50:21,240 --> 00:50:22,280
I'm not a girl.

674
00:50:23,520 --> 00:50:26,400
I'm not doing this
because I think you're a girl.

675
00:50:28,760 --> 00:50:30,040
But because…

676
00:50:31,160 --> 00:50:32,400
you're my boyfriend.

677
00:50:35,360 --> 00:50:37,400
Whatever.

678
00:50:39,400 --> 00:50:40,800
I'm gonna dig in.

679
00:50:41,920 --> 00:50:42,960
Go on.

680
00:50:43,360 --> 00:50:44,760
Here I go.

681
00:50:45,320 --> 00:50:47,320
I've been waiting for this.

682
00:50:49,640 --> 00:50:50,760
Watch me.

683
00:50:53,840 --> 00:50:55,240
So thick.

684
00:50:58,480 --> 00:50:59,600
Delicious?

685
00:51:00,280 --> 00:51:01,160
Absolutely.

686
00:51:01,520 --> 00:51:02,680
You eat too.

687
00:51:04,160 --> 00:51:05,360
It's okay.

688
00:51:05,680 --> 00:51:08,440
I'm waiting for my grilled mackerel.

689
00:51:10,240 --> 00:51:13,240
What for?
You haven't eaten since last night.

690
00:51:14,440 --> 00:51:15,360
Here.

691
00:51:16,000 --> 00:51:17,920
Eat it or you'll starve to death.

692
00:51:19,640 --> 00:51:20,800
You eat first.

693
00:51:22,160 --> 00:51:23,280
I'm not a girl.

694
00:51:23,760 --> 00:51:26,240
I won't let you
be the only one to apologize.

695
00:51:26,640 --> 00:51:27,960
I'm sorry about before.

696
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:29,960
Here.

697
00:51:31,320 --> 00:51:32,480
Eat it.

698
00:51:34,680 --> 00:51:36,120
That's it.

699
00:51:36,760 --> 00:51:37,680
How is it?

700
00:51:38,400 --> 00:51:39,400
Yummy?

701
00:51:43,600 --> 00:51:44,440
More, eat more.

702
00:51:45,240 --> 00:51:46,760
It's tasty.

703
00:51:47,600 --> 00:51:48,440
Eat.

704
00:51:50,560 --> 00:51:51,880
That's it.

705
00:51:53,120 --> 00:51:53,960
Want more?

706
00:51:54,840 --> 00:51:56,200
No, thanks.

707
00:51:56,760 --> 00:51:58,720
Why aren't you eating? It's not tasty?

708
00:51:58,800 --> 00:51:59,800
It's tasty.

709
00:52:04,360 --> 00:52:05,760
You sure are comfortable.

710
00:52:09,440 --> 00:52:10,640
I'll wait over there.

711
00:52:11,840 --> 00:52:12,960
Type, wait.

712
00:52:14,880 --> 00:52:16,080
Let me go.

713
00:52:17,640 --> 00:52:19,160
You'll run away if I let go.

714
00:52:21,000 --> 00:52:22,480
This is not only for me.

715
00:52:25,160 --> 00:52:27,320
Okay, I'll stay.

716
00:52:28,120 --> 00:52:30,360
But don't say anything stupid
like last time.

717
00:52:32,360 --> 00:52:33,680
What did I say?

718
00:52:34,800 --> 00:52:37,120
The saleslady was the one
who got it wrong.

719
00:52:38,720 --> 00:52:40,520
But if she mentions it again…

720
00:52:41,720 --> 00:52:44,120
this time, she'll be right.

721
00:52:45,520 --> 00:52:46,600
Whatever.

722
00:52:47,760 --> 00:52:49,840
Which one do you like?

723
00:52:51,200 --> 00:52:53,240
They're all the same.

724
00:52:53,840 --> 00:52:55,160
They're not the same, sir.

725
00:52:55,880 --> 00:52:57,760
The materials are different.

726
00:52:58,120 --> 00:53:02,240
Wait… you were here before, right?
I remember you.

727
00:53:03,560 --> 00:53:04,560
Yes.

728
00:53:08,840 --> 00:53:10,320
Would you like to sit on it?

729
00:53:11,840 --> 00:53:13,280
You should do it.

730
00:53:13,560 --> 00:53:15,560
-We'll sleep together anyway.
-Tharn!

731
00:53:17,800 --> 00:53:20,600
We share a dorm room. Am I wrong?

732
00:53:20,720 --> 00:53:22,320
You're living in the same room?

733
00:53:23,440 --> 00:53:24,680
That's right.

734
00:53:25,120 --> 00:53:28,280
That's why we're looking
for a new mattress for…

735
00:53:29,080 --> 00:53:30,360
our new room.

736
00:53:32,240 --> 00:53:35,520
Then, I suggest a rubber mattress.

737
00:53:35,960 --> 00:53:39,800
The price is higher,
but so is the quality.

738
00:53:40,840 --> 00:53:43,880
Because the weight of two men on the bed…

739
00:53:44,360 --> 00:53:46,600
is heavier than women.

740
00:53:46,760 --> 00:53:51,440
The spring mattress may squeak
when you move.

741
00:53:52,840 --> 00:53:56,560
It also has a sagging problem
and can't support heavy weight.

742
00:53:56,640 --> 00:53:58,200
So I don't recommend it.

743
00:53:58,440 --> 00:54:01,360
-Or would you like to try a foam mattress?
-Foam mattress?

744
00:54:01,640 --> 00:54:04,560
Yes, it's cheaper
than the rubber mattress.

745
00:54:04,720 --> 00:54:07,520
It provides support just as well,
but it's less durable.

746
00:54:07,720 --> 00:54:08,840
I see.

747
00:54:09,920 --> 00:54:13,840
Then, I'll let you choose.
I have to take this call.

748
00:54:14,080 --> 00:54:15,280
You're leaving me alone?

749
00:54:18,560 --> 00:54:19,400
Okay.

750
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:23,520
Hello, San.

751
00:54:23,800 --> 00:54:25,360
<i>Don't "hello San" me.</i>

752
00:54:26,160 --> 00:54:27,560
<i>You bailed on me yesterday.</i>

753
00:54:28,560 --> 00:54:30,080
I didn't bail on you.

754
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,360
You were planning to meet with Thorn.

755
00:54:32,520 --> 00:54:34,560
<i>You know I want to see you.</i>

756
00:54:37,840 --> 00:54:38,880
So…

757
00:54:39,200 --> 00:54:40,360
what do you want?

758
00:54:40,960 --> 00:54:42,720
<i>Do you want anything in particular?</i>

759
00:54:46,240 --> 00:54:47,880
No, I don't want anything.

760
00:54:48,560 --> 00:54:50,160
I don't want to impose on you.

761
00:54:50,360 --> 00:54:51,720
<i>Come on, Tharn.</i>

762
00:54:51,960 --> 00:54:54,760
<i>You know I hate to buy</i>
<i>random birthday presents.</i>

763
00:54:55,440 --> 00:54:57,360
<i>So? What do you want?</i>

764
00:54:58,600 --> 00:55:00,200
I really don't want anything.

765
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:04,280
<i>Don't complain</i>
<i>if you don't like my present.</i>

766
00:55:04,520 --> 00:55:06,040
Okay.

767
00:55:33,760 --> 00:55:35,840
What's the matter?

768
00:55:39,520 --> 00:55:41,560
Are you free before the semester starts?

769
00:55:43,360 --> 00:55:45,200
Before the semester starts…

770
00:55:52,840 --> 00:55:54,160
You found out.

771
00:56:04,560 --> 00:56:06,040
Before the semester starts…

772
00:56:07,960 --> 00:56:09,320
I'm free in the afternoon.

773
00:56:09,840 --> 00:56:11,560
I have to go home in the evening.

774
00:56:12,280 --> 00:56:13,440
Go home?

775
00:56:15,520 --> 00:56:17,240
It's my mom's rule.

776
00:56:17,720 --> 00:56:21,400
On birthdays, we can celebrate
with whoever we want.

777
00:56:22,400 --> 00:56:25,280
But dinnertime is family time.

778
00:56:26,200 --> 00:56:28,920
That's why I must have dinner
with my family.

779
00:56:30,520 --> 00:56:31,480
So…

780
00:56:32,040 --> 00:56:33,800
what if you have a boyfriend?

781
00:56:34,480 --> 00:56:35,640
If I have a boyfriend…

782
00:56:36,160 --> 00:56:39,600
my mom allows me to bring my boyfriend.

783
00:56:40,640 --> 00:56:46,320
But if my boyfriend asks
why he's not my priority…

784
00:56:48,520 --> 00:56:49,840
my mom would say that…

785
00:56:50,040 --> 00:56:54,200
she was the one who endured the pain
of giving birth to me.

786
00:56:55,160 --> 00:56:59,520
That's why she has the right to choose.

787
00:57:01,600 --> 00:57:03,360
My mom also says that…

788
00:57:04,280 --> 00:57:07,480
if my boyfriend's being unreasonable,
I should tell him this,

789
00:57:08,960 --> 00:57:13,480
"If you don't love your family,
how can you love someone else?"

790
00:57:14,760 --> 00:57:16,120
Therefore…

791
00:57:18,840 --> 00:57:20,040
come with me.

792
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:24,520
Come to my house on my birthday.

793
00:57:26,040 --> 00:57:27,160
Did you forget that…

794
00:57:27,640 --> 00:57:29,000
My family knows.

795
00:57:36,200 --> 00:57:37,200
I…

796
00:57:40,840 --> 00:57:42,680
came out when I was in 12th grade.

797
00:57:44,880 --> 00:57:46,840
So my family knows…

798
00:57:49,360 --> 00:57:50,680
I'm gay.

799
00:58:00,480 --> 00:58:02,240
This is not the time to be horny.

800
00:58:02,920 --> 00:58:04,440
We need to talk this over.

801
00:58:06,760 --> 00:58:09,960
I think we're done talking.

802
00:58:11,760 --> 00:58:13,400
You'll come to my house.

803
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:15,840
It's a birthday present for me.

804
00:58:16,000 --> 00:58:18,000
I didn't say anything about it.

805
00:58:18,760 --> 00:58:20,240
I won't go to your house.

806
00:58:21,640 --> 00:58:25,160
Even though your family knows
what you are…

807
00:58:26,720 --> 00:58:31,400
I'm not shameless enough to go there
and declare I'm your boyfriend.

808
00:58:34,160 --> 00:58:37,000
Your parents may accept you
for who you are,

809
00:58:38,040 --> 00:58:41,160
but it doesn't mean they'll accept
their son's sex buddy.

810
00:58:46,920 --> 00:58:48,000
Type…

811
00:58:50,200 --> 00:58:51,160
you…

812
00:58:52,080 --> 00:58:53,120
are my boyfriend.

813
00:58:54,240 --> 00:58:55,640
Not my sex buddy.

814
00:58:58,040 --> 00:58:59,760
Just tell me what you want.

815
00:59:00,760 --> 00:59:02,280
But I won't go to your house.

816
00:59:03,480 --> 00:59:06,160
I already told you what I wanted.

817
00:59:07,040 --> 00:59:10,160
When did you say it?
I've been paying attention the whole time.

818
00:59:10,760 --> 00:59:14,040
I told you, but you didn't listen.

